Returns:

createSnapshot

public ZFSObject createSnapshot(java.lang.String snapshotName,
                                boolean recursive)
Takes a snapshot atomically and recursively.

Parameters:
snapshotName - Snapshot name, like 'monday' or 'before-test' or whatever.
recursive - Recursively create snapshots of all descendant datasets. Snapshots are taken atomically, so that all recursive snapshots correspond to the same moment in time.
Returns:
The snapshot that was just created.

clone

public ZFSObject clone(java.lang.String fullDestinationName)
Creates a clone from this snapshot. This method fails if this ZFSObject is not a snapshot.
